  "market_context": "Bearish trend on GBPJPY 1H with prior break of structure, cleared liquidity above equal highs, then pullback forming equal lows at 181.200, followed by upward move to fill a fair value gap and reverse from a fresh supply zone.",
  "key_observation": "After breaking structure and forming equal lows, price swept sellside liquidity below the lows, then rallied to fill a fair value gap before reversing sharply from an unmitigated supply zone.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified a bearish market structure with multiple breaks of structure confirming downtrend.",
    "Step 2: Noted price formed equal lows (at 181.200) after downward impulse, indicating potential SSL zone.",
    "Step 3: Observed price swept external sellside liquidity below the equal lows, then reversed upward.",
    "Step 4: Tracked price moving up to fill a fair value gap created during prior mitigation, entering an unmitigated supply zone.",
    "Step 5: Looked for reversal confirmation (e.g., change of character) on lower timeframe near the supply zone for optimal entry.",
    "Step 6: Confirmed bearish continuation after rejection from the supply zone, initiating another break of structure."
  ],
